Name: Waroeng "adji"
Review Text: Good Indonesian restaurant in Slotervaart Amsterdam West. I ordered Indonesian Yellow Rice (Nasi Kuning) and it was yummy.  The cendol (glutinous rice with cocos melk and palm sugar) was also good.

Name: Waroeng "adji"
Review Text: Delicious and Good quality food at great prices.

Name: Waroeng "adji"
Review Text: It may be a take-out shop, but it serves good, authentic, wide variety and homey indonesian food. It also sells some of the home-made sauces and ingredients used for indonesian dishes. Above all, the lady at the shop is very friendly & helpful. If you want a quick fix for indonesian food & a taste of home, this is the place to come

Name: Waroeng "adji"
Review Text: Delicious and great value, wide variety of authentic dishes, one of the best Indonesian restaurants I have visited. Take away possible.
